d-3c46-9f95-ab0f-f9d407d668b4"}, "input": {"input": ["继发性妄想:是发生在其他病理心理基础（如感知、情感、记忆、思维、智能等障碍）的背景上发生、发展，而妄想的产生是对原发障碍的解释，原发障碍消失以后妄想也将随之消退。", "强迫思维:", "HYPERPROSEXIA:Hyperprosexia refers to a significant increase in active attention, often associated with delusions, where patients pay heightened attention to details related to their delusions.\"", "HYPOPROSEXIA:Hypoprosexia is the weakening of both active and passive attention, making it difficult to focus on a single object for an extended period, often leading to memory issues.\"", "TRANSFERENCE OF ATTENTION:Transference of attention occurs when active attention cannot be sustained, and passive attention increases but also cannot be maintained, leading to frequent shifts in focus.\"", "APROSEXIA:Aprosexia is the difficulty in maintaining active attention, characterized by poor stability and easy distraction, often resulting in ineffective learning or reading.\"", "FIXATION OF ATTENTION:Fixation of attention is the increased stability of attention, often seen in individuals with persistent delusions who focus intensely on the content of their delusions.\"", "NARROWING OF ATTENTION:Narrowing of attention refers to a significant reduction in the range of attention, where active attention is weakened, and other stimuli fail to capture attention.\"", "BLUNTING OF ATTENTION:Blunting of attention is the difficulty in quickly and effectively focusing attention, often seen when responding to a series of questions, leading to slower responses.\"", "HYPERMNESIA:Hypermnesia is the enhanced ability to recall details of past events, even those that were previously considered unimportant or forgotten.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}